---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Data Processing Agreement"
  description="DataBreef's Data Processing Agreement (DPA) for GDPR compliance — covering roles, obligations, and sub-processors."
  lastUpdated="April 2026"
>
  <p>
    This Data Processing Agreement ("<strong>DPA</strong>") forms part of the agreement between
    DataBreef ("<strong>Processor</strong>") and the customer entity that has agreed to our
    <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a> ("<strong>Controller</strong>"). It governs the processing
    of personal data in the context of the DataBreef service in accordance with the GDPR and other
    applicable data protection laws.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Definitions</h2>
  <p>
    Terms used in this DPA have the meanings set out in the GDPR (Regulation (EU) 2016/679).
    "<strong>Personal Data</strong>" means any information relating to an identified or identifiable
    natural person that the Controller submits to the Service. "<strong>Processing</strong>" has
    the meaning given in Article 4(2) GDPR.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Roles of the Parties</h2>
  <p>
    The Controller determines the purposes and means of processing personal data in relation to
    its use of DataBreef. DataBreef acts as a Processor, processing personal data only on the
    Controller's documented instructions and only to the extent necessary to provide the Service.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Important:</strong> DataBreef operates in strictly read-only mode. DataBreef introspects
    database <em>schema</em> (structure, relationships, column names) — not row-level personal data
    contained within your tables. Connection strings are the primary personal data DataBreef processes.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Processor Obligations</h2>
  <p>DataBreef agrees to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Process personal data only on documented instructions from the Controller</li>
    <li>Ensure persons authorized to process personal data are bound by confidentiality</li>
    <li>Implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures (Article 32 GDPR)</li>
    <li>Assist the Controller in responding to data subject rights requests</li>
    <li>Delete or return all personal data upon termination of the Service</li>
    <li>Provide all information necessary to demonstrate compliance with this DPA</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Sub-Processors</h2>
  <p>
    DataBreef uses the following sub-processors to provide the Service. The Controller grants
    general authorization for DataBreef to engage sub-processors, subject to the conditions below.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Vercel</strong> (hosting, US/EU) — application and API infrastructure</li>
    <li><strong>Neon</strong> (database, US) — application database for account and session data</li>
    <li><strong>Stripe</strong> (payments, US) — billing and subscription management</li>
    <li><strong>Sentry</strong> (monitoring, US) — error tracking (PII scrubbing enabled)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    DataBreef will notify the Controller at least 14 days before adding new sub-processors.
    The Controller may object to a new sub-processor within that period.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Security Measures</h2>
  <p>DataBreef implements the following measures as required by Article 32 GDPR:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>AES-256-GCM encryption for connection strings at rest</li>
    <li>TLS 1.2+ for all data in transit</li>
    <li>Role-based access controls and least-privilege principles</li>
    <li>Regular security assessments and dependency auditing</li>
    <li>Incident response procedures with 72-hour breach notification</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. International Data Transfers</h2>
  <p>
    Where DataBreef transfers personal data outside the European Economic Area, it does so on the
    basis of Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) as approved by the European Commission, or
    another adequacy mechanism recognized under applicable data protection law.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Data Retention & Deletion</h2>
  <p>
    Upon termination of the Service or upon written request, DataBreef will delete or return all
    personal data within 30 days, unless retention is required by applicable law. A deletion
    certificate is available upon request.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Audit Rights</h2>
  <p>
    DataBreef will provide the Controller with all information necessary to demonstrate compliance
    with this DPA. The Controller may conduct audits or inspections with reasonable notice
    (30 days minimum) and at the Controller's expense.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Governing Law</h2>
  <p>
    This DPA is governed by the laws of [Jurisdiction — TBD], consistent with the governing law
    in the main Terms of Service.
  </p>

  <div class="legal-contact">
    <h2>Executing a Signed DPA</h2>
    <p>
      Enterprise customers requiring a countersigned DPA should contact us. We will provide a
      signed copy within 5 business days.
    </p>
    <p><strong>DataBreef Legal</strong> — <a href="mailto:legal@databreef.io">legal@databreef.io</a></p>
  </div>
</LegalLayout>
